parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HID headlight actuator/ballast can cause the headlights to become inoperative, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: One or both headlights are not functioning
reduced illumination range
difficulty driving at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The insufficient illumination range of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, making it difficult to drive at night, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Short range of headlight illumination
difficulty driving at night
inability to see road ahead.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intense glare from xenon headlamps can cause discomfort and distraction to oncoming drivers, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Blinding glare from oncoming vehicles
discomfort or distraction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning indicator is illuminated on the instrument panel
the airbag warning indicator is constantly illuminated
the airbag warning indicator is intermittently illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks, especially if the vehicle is stranded in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the starter motor is burned out
the ignition switch is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly address the recall can lead to continued vehicle problems, including the ignition switch malfunction, and potentially cause safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle continues to experience issues despite recall repairs
the dealership fails to acknowledge the recall
the recall is not properly performed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly address the crank position sensor weld recall can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the crank position sensor is faulty
the recall was not properly performed.
